details.detail:
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Cut the fries into 1/4 to 1/3-inch thick julienne. Soak in water for 20 minutes.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In a heavy (such as cast iron) dutch oven or deep fryer, heat oil to 300 F.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To make the fries&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Completely dry the potatoes just before you add them to the hot oil.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Cook potatoes 3-4 minutes (should be cooked on the inside with no color on the outside)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Remove and put on backing rack above a baking sheet to cool.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Bring oil temp up to 375 F.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Put the fries back into the oil and cook until golden brown.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Remove and drain on baking rack once again. Salt to taste.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Final assembly&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Toss in beef gravy and top with the cheese&amp;nbsp;curds. &amp;nbsp;Serve immediately while the fries are still crisp.&lt;/p&gt;
